This paper deals with the task of cross-lingual entity alignment using embedding-based approaches. It combines graph convolutional networks (GCNs) and a pretrained multilingual BERT model to encode entities from multilingual knowledge graphs (KGs) into the same vector space. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Computation and Language (cs.CL), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Databases (cs.DB).
